data.title: Once a great place to eat
data.text: Used to be one of my favorite restaurants to have great Mexican food but after many administrative changes they change  recipes and cut corner, no the food is terrible and expensive, portions are extra small, customer service was also out the window

data.title: Great Food
data.text:
My husband and I have been going to El Torito in Milpitas since they closed
the one in Santa Clara.  We have gone to the Sunday buffet, lunches and
dinners.
99% of the time they open the doors for us and they take us to the table that
is close to everything.  The buffet is great and it is only $11.99.  You can spend
a couple of hours just enjoying your breakfast.

Enjoy.

data.title: Not great- not horrible
data.text:
I was in town from NC to celebrate my birthday with my twin sister. We decided on El Torito for location and nostalgic reasons. We used to love going to the one near Vallco so many years ago. 
My mom and I, and my sister and one of her sons each shared the fajitas (18-19$ each). Her husband orders the Tuesday special all you can eat enchiladas. Her other son ordered a macncheese/shrimp/cheese burrito (18.99$). 
1. Fajitas were ok. Nice presentation but not a lot of guacamole or corn chutney?  Steak and shrimp was good. Chicken and shrimp was ok too. A lot of onions!!!
2. Shrimp/macncheese and cheese burrito was ok- but he was still hungry afterwards (growing 16 year old).  I thought it was over priced. 
3 Enchiladas were ok- nothing special. 
Our waitress was not engaging. She barely smiled and was always rushing off quickly. ( restaurant was not busy). My mom told her it was our birthday so they brought out 2 fried ice cream (reg $ 5) in a margarita dish with a candle and they sang Happy birthday. 
So the fried ice cream was good but we thought the toppings was Special K or another type of cereal. Small scoop. I had fried ice cream in Raleigh recently and it was so delicious. Fried outer coat in a fried she'll with chocolate drizzle and it was enough for 3 people! 
Anyway. Our bill for 6 people came to approx $110. 
I gave it 3 stars because it wasn't horrible but I would not rush to go back. 
Have a great day!

data.title: Good food
data.text: We were on the road for awhile. Check in to our hotel. Had dinner here.Clean fast and great food. We even got a free desert, Wow, Thanks.

data.title: Still one of my favorite Mexican restaurants
data.text:
Sizzling fajitas with steak are the best. Not healthy, but darn tasty. Chips and salsa are always fresh. Service is good. This El Torito is clean, but the dining room could use a makeover. Furniture is a bit dated.

Service is very good and consistent. I eat here all the time, so my review is based on a lot of experience.

data.title: Decent Mexican meal
data.text: It's a nice location and chips and salsa are always fresh. Rest of the fare is above average. It does get crowded on weekends, so call and make reservation.

data.title: Real Mexican food!
data.text:
every time that I am in town I expend one night there. Ask for a margarita just to start the dinner and pick one of the fajitas pates.

Service is friendly and if you have doubt will help you to find the right plate.

data.title: Perfect after a long travel day
data.text:
We ate here on arrival day of a long flight.  It is walking distance from our hotel.  We arrived around 5:00pm and the restaurant looked to be transitioning to the dinner hour. The waiter seem a bit brusque at first and I had to restrain from saying something negative about his responses. He came around towards the end of the dinner.  We ordered fahitas, quesadillas, and fahita salad.  It took longer than we expected for a near empty restaurant, but there was a large table near us that was probably in the queue.  We had 2 rounds of chips and salsa which was very good. 

When our meals arrived, I was pleasantly surprised that the fahita salad was very good which was served with tableside dressing with nice slices of avocado. The flour tortilla was also very good and much better than east coast restaurants. (nod to west coast Mexican influence).  I also ordered a mango margarita which was syrupy and disappointing.  However, everyone was satisfied with their meals.

data.title: If you want to watch Mexican Soccer this is your place...
data.text: In general the Mexican food is average, the place is most oriented to watch TV specially the Mexican Soccer Cup, in general the place is cool, I belive too many tables in the area but You probably noticed those Mexican Restaurants are always full.

data.title: Sometimes One Just Has to Leave and Go Else Where
data.text:
OK - we decided to stop by Milpitas El Torito's as they were having a $3.00 Margarita week-end.  We let them know that when we came to be seated. It took them about 10 minutes to find a place to seat us as the place was about 20 per cent full of people and there were a lot of empty tables.  Each of these tables were nicely cleaned and set up for customers.

So we "understand" the wait as its good to stand prior to dining..  After 10 minutes 3 people actually tried to help us find a table as neither one knew if we had been helped.  (hello - usually there is one attentive person to help people when they arrive).

Then we got seated.  And again 10 minutes.  No chips and salsa arrived.  No server showed up.

Then the server showed up and we asked about their margaritas and they said - well. You cannot order them here as they are only for the bar. And instead of helping, just walked away.

So, we got up and went to the bar. It was about 20 per cent full of people.  Again, nobody seemed to care about paying customers.   And we found one table which did not have an amazing amount of dirty dishes on it.   We sat down and I realized why - there was a constant cold draft coming through the door from the patio area.   Again, we asked about clearing another table and we were met with - How dare you show up 90 minutes before we close type stare.....

And at that point, I looked at my husband and said - We will go to the one in Santa Clara, even its close to Levi's Stadium (which was having the outdoor ice hockey match).  We drove the short distance had an excellent dinner at clean tables with staff that cared; good chips and salsa; and yep 2 $3.00 Margaritas each.   

Its like night and day at the Milpitas Restaurant - sorry, but somehow they seemed to have slipped amazingly downhill.  So my very rare one star for TERRIBLE.

Yep - we are out of here (hope it improves). There are other Mexican restaurants in Milpitas where customer is iimportant and the food is better.  Baja Cactus and Cafe Azteca come to mind. We would have gone there if it were not for the $3.00 Margaritas.'

data.title: Disappointing
data.text:
Had a group of 7...Friday evening...they were not very busy, should have been a sign!
Slow service, our waiter seemed to disappear at times.
Food was just OK. 
When waiter brought our change (we had separate checks) he kept any extra coin change versus bringing it to us and letting us decide what tip he got.
Not sure it is legal to keep the change without asking!!

data.title: Good food slow service
data.text: The food tastes good if you're willing to tolerate slow service. Restaurant appears to be understaffed

data.title: Enjoyable Place for Mexican Food, Taco Tuesdays Also
data.text:
I like their shrimp enchiladas here with a margarita of course.   Their chips and salsa are also good.   We have also gone for Taco Tuesdays - very reasonable price for good tacos and drinks in their bar section.

The restaurant has a nice atmosphere; good seating in the bar; and patio section as well.

Parking is in their lot -there is a lot nearby if it is full.

Service has been fine here - but do plan to have a leisurely dinner as the pacing of delivery allows you to enjoy the chips and salsa and drinks, before dinner arrives.

data.title: West mex? Cali mex?
data.text:
What do you call this type of food in the west coast?? 

Call ahead to make sure they are serving from the menu when you plan on going. The have an all you can eat buffet prior to the time they begin serving off the menu. Never experienced that before. I liked the little scoop of cornbread with my entree. (Never had that before) Plates were over priced in my opinion but I don't live in Cali...Food wasn't as authentic as I hoped it to be. I'm from tx so if I order a crispy beef taco then im expecting ground beef not pulled chucks of beef (brisket style). The type of beef was not listed on the menu. Not my style at all but bad. Coronas were $6 and warm. I asked for my beer dressed and I had a LEMON put in it. 
Dressed= Salt + Lime 
Well at least that's how they do it everywhere else I've been. I expected much more and got a lot less.

data.title: Extremely slow service and badly overcooked food
data.text:
The initial experience when we arrived was nice. We sat outside and ordered Margaritas to got with the chips and salsa that they brought. The salsa was really nice and the Margaritas were acceptable, but not great. It didn't take too long for our server to take our order.

The food took the best part of an hour to come out and when it did it was so dry and inedible that it seems to me like it was sat under a heat lamp for 20+ minutes after it came out of the kitchen. The server never came back to check on how the food was so I asked at the bar to speak to her to explain the situation. In their defense they removed the uneaten food from the bill without a fuss, but as it had taken almost an hour to get the initial food I didn't have time to wait for anything else. I ended up leaving without eating anything other than some chips and salsa.

There is always plenty of competition for Mexican restaurants and there are many other places that I will visit rather than this one based on my experience.

data.title: Baseball weekend at Twin Creeks
data.text: Service was very slow and it took a while to receive our food.  We had a large crowd but we were constantly asking for water our to refill our drinks.  The place was not crowded at all.  Our orders were all messed up as well.

data.title: This place continues to please
data.text: Even after 10 years, this is my go to place for lunch, dinner, drinks, etc with friends and fam. Service is always great and the food is obviously amazing. I wish there were more locations in California, but any time I'm in NorCal, this is my first stop!

data.title: El Torrito lunch buffet
data.text: El Torrito has a wonderful weekly lunch buffet. Plenty of seating and food is kept both warm and fresh. Love their thin tortilla chips and tropical ice tea.

data.title: My Son Ate Vegetables! :)
data.text: Decent price for good food. The grilled veggies side was a hit with my son. I will be trying to copy them.

data.title: great
data.text: the Margaritas and the food was excellent, service was ok was not very croweded, salsa was very good as well, the oberall experience was very good
